'''''Speeches of a Most Worthy Sage''''' was a [[book]] penned by [[Tharghin Ammatar|Tharghin "Threeboots" Ammatar]] in the {{YearlinkName|1329}}.

{{quote|''There are no endings save death, only pauses for breath, and new beginnings. Always, new beginnings... it's why the world grows ever more crowded, ye see. So remember, now–there are no endings, only beginnings. There; simple enough, isn't it? Elegant, too.''|Tharghin "Threeboots" Ammatar}}
